d dependency does NOT automatically fail its dependents -- they remain blocked.\n- There should be a way to inspect a task's dependency status.\n# Phase 8: Concurrency Control\n\nAdd per-queue limits on how many tasks can be processed at the same time.\n\n## Requirements\n\n- Each queue can have a maximum concurrency setting that limits how many tasks can be in a processing state simultaneously.\n- If the concurrency limit is reached, retrieving a task returns `null` even if pending tasks are available.\n- Completing or failing a task frees up a concurrency slot.\n- By default, queues have no concurrency limit (unlimited).\n- There should be a way to set and query the concurrency limit and current active count for a queue.\n- Concurrency interacts correctly with priority ordering -- the highest-priority available task is still chosen, subject to the concurrency limit.\n# Phase 9: Progress Tracking and Cancellation\n\nAdd the ability to report progress on running tasks and to cancel tasks.\n\n## Requirements\n\n- A processing task can report its progress as a percentage (0-100) with an optional message.\n- There should be a way to query a task's current progress.\n- Listeners can subscribe to progress updates for a task and receive notifications when progress changes.\n- Subscriptions should be cancellable (unsubscribe).\n- Tasks in pending or processing state can be cancelled.\n- Cancelled pending tasks are removed from the queue and will not be returned.\n- Cancelled processing tasks have their status updated accordingly.\n- Cancelled tasks are never retried, even if they had retries remaining.\n# Phase 10: Recurring Tasks\n\nAdd the ability to schedule tasks that recur on a regular interval using simple cron-like expressions.\n\n## Requirements\n\n- A schedule associates a cron expression with a queue and a task template (the payload to use each time).\n- Support a simple subset of cron expressions:\n  - `*/N * * * *` -- every N minutes\n  - `0 * * * *` -- every hour on the hour\n  - `0 0 * * *` -- every day at midnight\n- There should be a way to create, remove, and list active schedules.\n- A manual \"tick\" or \"check\" mechanism should evaluate all active schedules and enqueue tasks for any that are due. This is used for testing.\n- Once enqueued, recurring tasks are regular tasks subject to all other queue rules.\n- Removing a schedule stops future occurrences from being created.\n# Phase 11: Middleware Pipeline\n\nAdd a middleware system that can intercept and transform tasks as they are processed.\n\n## Requirements\n\n- Middleware functions can be registered per queue.\n- When a task is processed, it passes through all registered middleware in order before reaching the final handler.\n- Each middleware receives the task and a \"next\" function. Calling \"next\" passes control to the next middleware (or the handler).\n- If a middleware does NOT call \"next\", the task processing is skipped.\n- Middleware can modify the task (e.g., adding metadata or transforming the payload).\n- If a middleware throws an error, the task should be marked as failed.\n- A processing function/handler can be registered per queue. It is invoked after all middleware have run.\n- Each queue has its own independent middleware stack.\n# Phase 12: Graceful Shutdown\n\nAdd the ability to shut down the task queue system in an orderly fashion.\n\n## Requirements\n\n- A shutdown operation should signal the system to stop accepting new tasks.\n- After shutdown is initiated, attempting to add new tasks should produce an error.\n- The shutdown should wait for all currently-processing tasks to finish, up to a configurable timeout.\n- If processing tasks do not complete within the timeout, they should be force-cancelled.\n- Callbacks can be registered to run during the shutdown process.\n- The shutdown should produce a summary indicating how many tasks completed, how many were force-cancelled, and how long the shutdown took.\n- Calling shutdown multiple times should be safe and return the same result.\n- If no tasks are processing, shutdown should complete immediately.","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
